menu "RadioCore Options"


config RADIOCORE_ID_STRING
    string "Default Radio ID (IDxxx;)"
    default "023"
    help
        Default radio ID string returned by ID; queries when not overridden.
        For TS-590SG this is typically 023. For TS-2000, use 020.

config RADIOCORE_FV_STRING
    string "Default Firmware Version (FVy.yy;)"
    default "1.04"
    help
        Default firmware version string returned by FV; queries when not overridden.

config TRANSVERTER_SUPPORT
    bool "Enable transverter support"
    default y
    help
        Enable transverter functionality including EX056 menu handling,
        XO offset commands, and transverter macros. Required for use with
        transverters and microwave equipment.
        
        When disabled, transverter-related features are compiled out to
        save flash/RAM for systems that don't need transverter functionality.

config TRANSVERTER_DISPLAY_OFFSET
    bool "Compile transverter XO offset to FA/FB display support"
    default y
    depends on TRANSVERTER_SUPPORT
    help
        When enabled, compiles in support for applying XO transverter offset
        to FA/FB frequencies reported to the USB host.

        The feature is controlled at runtime via UIXD command:
        - UIXD1; enables offset display (FA/FB include XO offset)
        - UIXD0; disables offset display (strict TS-590SG compatibility)

        This option is only available when transverter support is enabled.

config RADIOCORE_EMULATE_TS2000
    bool "Emulate Kenwood TS-2000 responses (ID019, FV1.20)"
    default n
    help
        When enabled, ID; responds with ID020; and FV; responds with FV1.20; to
        better align with TS-2000 behavior, useful for transverter workflows.

## Polling functionality removed
## The following options were intentionally deleted to eliminate internal polling:
## - RADIOCORE_SMART_POLLING and related TTL presets
## - RADIOCORE_METER_POLLING and burst polling controls
## - RADIOCORE_INTERNAL_POLLING and SYNC interval/activity tuning

# Auto-readback after SET (replaces polling for confirmation)
config RADIOCORE_AUTO_QUERY_AFTER_SET
    bool "Send READ after SET (auto-readback)"
    default y
    help
        When enabled, the router automatically sends the corresponding READ
        command to the radio after processing a local SET (from USB or Display).
        This confirms that the radio applied the change and updates local state
        from the authoritative source. These READs bypass cache TTL logic.

config RADIOCORE_AUTO_QUERY_RESPECT_AI
    bool "Skip auto-readback when AI2/AI4 is active"
    default n
    help
        When enabled, auto-readback is suppressed if the radio is in AI2/AI4
        mode (since the radio will broadcast updates itself). Leave disabled
        to always confirm via a READ after SET.

config RADIOCORE_MANUAL_KEEPALIVE
    bool "Enable Manual KeepAlive (RRC-1258 compatibility)"
    default n
    help
        When enabled, the interface will periodically send PS1; commands to
        radioSerial to maintain the RRC-1258 connection. This prevents the
        RRC unit from timing out when no external commands are being sent.

config RADIOCORE_MANUAL_KEEPALIVE_TIME
    int "Manual KeepAlive interval (milliseconds)"
    default 1000
    range 100 60000
    depends on RADIOCORE_MANUAL_KEEPALIVE
    help
        Time interval in milliseconds between PS1; keepalive transmissions.
        Default is 1000ms (1 second). Range: 100ms to 60s.

endmenu
